A would-be robber has been killed in a shootout at a shopping centre in Reservoir Hills, KwaZulu Natal on Tuesday.It is reported that the man was in his 30s.On arrival paramedics found a number of local law enforcement officers already in attendance.Paramedics were led into a shop, where they found the man, believed to be one of the suspects, lying behind one of the counters. Paramedics found the man had sustained numerous gunshot wounds and was in a critical condition. A fter 20 minutes, the man succumbed to his injuries and was declared dead on the scene, according to ER24. Police are investigating.-TNA Reporter 